@node "Errors" "HTTPJ v2.00 - Error codes"

   @{b}HTTPJ@{ub} returns a large number of return codes, which permit to know the exact reason of program termination. This is very useful for the creation of @{b}batch files@{ub} or @{b}ARexx scripts{ub}.


Error codes generated by @{b}HTTPJ@{ub} are:

@{b}    0 - OK@{ub}

   The program hasn't encountered problems and has downloaded the document.

@{b}    1 - Document not modified@{ub}

   This error code is returned when the @{b}Update@{ub} argument is used, and the specified document isn't newer than the local copy.  The program is terminated without problems, but the document hasn't downloaded.

@{b}    2 - Document moved@{ub}

   Document has been moved to another address but has been downloaded without problems.

@{b}    3 - User Break@{ub}

   Program execution was interrupted by the user.

@{b}   10 - No memory for buffer@{ub}

   There is not enough memory to allocate the transfer buffer.  The program terminates its execution.

@{b}   11 - Can't connect server@{ub}

   Connection to the specified server is not possible:  the TCP stack is not correctly started or the server isn't available.  The program terminates its execution.

@{b}   12 - Can't open output file@{ub}

   Creation of output file is not possible.  The program terminates its execution.

@{b}   13 - Error Reading remote File@{ub}

   An error reading the document from remote server has occurred. The program terminates its execution.

@{b}   14 - Error Writing Local File@{ub}

   An error writing of output file has occurred. The program terminates its execution.

@{b}   15 - Update need FileName parameter@{ub}

   The @{b}Update@{ub} argument also requires the name of the local copy, in order to compare the document creation date. The program terminates its execution.

@{b}   16 - Can't open log file@{ub}

   It isn't possible to open the log file specfied as argument.

@{b} · 17 - Can't open bsdsocket.library@{ub}

   It isn't possible to open the bsdsocket.library, probably because the TCP stack hasn't been activated.

@{b}   20 - Invalid arguments@{ub}

   Program was called with invalid or insufficient arguments.


In case of a remote server error, HTTPJ returns the error code from the server itself, which can be one of the following:

@{b}   401 - Unauthorized@{ub}

   Access to the document requires a password.

@{b}   404 - Not Found@{ub}

   Required document was not found.

@{b}   500 - Internal Server Error@{ub}

   Internal error of the server.

@{b}   501 - Not Implemented@{ub}

   The server can't interpret received commands.

@{b}   502 - Bad Gateway@{ub}

   Error in the Gateway management

@{b}   503 - Service Unavailable@{ub}

   Service isn't available.



@EndNode
